2.1(5) Hyper-parameter

Parameter Tuning

In essence, this is an optimization problem. 

Parameter and hyper-parameter:
ğœ† - after having the ğœ† value, we will be able to work on optimizing w using OLS or gradient descent.
hyper parameter: we cannot have the optimal value using OLS or gradient descent

In this chapter, we will explore how to tune the hyper-parameter:

GridSearchCV:
list all the possible combinations of parameters
run each models using these combinations
evaluate the model performance using metric (ROC, Accuracy etc)

RandomizedSearchCV:
when the increase of the number of hyper parameters to tune, gridsearchCV will take long.
RandomizedSearchCV reduce the computation cost

Application:
SVR
